    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.8.F.B.4</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Construct a function to model a linear relationship between two quantities. Determine the rate of change&amp;nbsp; and initial value of the function from a description of a relationship or from two (&lt;i&gt;x, y&lt;/i&gt;) values, including reading these from a table or from a graph. Interpret the rate of change and initial value of a linear function in terms of the situation it models, and in terms of its graph or a table of values.</Statement>
    </Statements>
